The Canva Editor consists of a main navigation, side panel, toolbar, canvas, and page controls. To focus on each section to learn more about each of them, press tab. To skip to the canvas, press "Ctrl+F2".

Skip navigation

This button opens the menu with all the options to share and print your design.
The main navigation contains buttons for document level options. To switch between buttons, use the left and right keys and to activate, press Enter. To skip to the canvas, press "Ctrl+F2".
Side Panel
The side panel is where you can apply templates or add elements. To skip to the canvas, press "Ctrl+F2".
Canvas
Change to bulleted list
The toolbar contains buttons to edit the selected element. To switch between buttons, use the left and right keys and to activate, press Enter. To skip to the canvas, press "Ctrl+F2".

Kickstart your ideas with the help of Canva's Magic Write. Magic Write uses the power of AI to follow your instructions and generate original copy from scratch. The more specific your request, the better the results. Here are a few ideas:
